# Fixes for SWu-IKEv2's get_res_ck_ik() (AT+CSIM EAP-AKA path) needed for
# real hardware SIMs beyond the upstream script's hardcoded assumptions:
#
#  1. SELECT with P2=0x00 (the upstream script's hardcoded value) is
#     rejected by some cards as "wrong P1/P2" (SW 6B00). P2=0x0C works
#     broadly. (Verified: Quectel EC200U + Vodafone/Vi India USIM.)
#  2. The upstream script hardcodes a generic USIM AID that doesn't match
#     every real card (verified different AIDs on two different SIMs from
#     two different operators: Vi India uses
#     A0000000871002FFF605FF89000001FF, Airtel India uses
#     A0000000871002FF49FFFF89030900FF). Rather than hardcoding either,
#     this discovers the real AID at runtime by reading EF_DIR (SELECT
#     3F00, SELECT 2F00, READ RECORD until a 61<len>4F<len><AID> template
#     whose AID starts with the 3GPP USIM RID A0000000871002 is found),
#     falling back to the original generic AID if discovery fails.
#  3. Some modems (verified: Quectel EC200U) auto-chain GET RESPONSE
#     internally and return the full AUTHENTICATE result with SW 9000
#     directly — there is no "61XX" marker to trigger the script's
#     follow-up GET RESPONSE call, which crashed with UnboundLocalError
#     (len_result unset). Skip that call when SW is already 9000 with full
#     data.
#  4. The upstream script's per-command retry fires a duplicate AT+CSIM
#     send if no OK/ERROR appears within 0.5s. A local/dummy AUTHENTICATE
#     answers fast, but a real network challenge's SIM computation can
#     legitimately take longer, so 0.5s spuriously retransmits while the
#     first response is still arriving — two overlapping "+CSIM: ..."
#     replies land in the same buffer and the text-based parser picks up a
#     fragment of AT command/response framing instead of hex APDU data
#     (observed: RES == "+CSIM: 4," -> crashes on unhexlify). Raised the
#     retry threshold to 5s and made the parser only accept fragments that
#     are actually valid hex, as a second line of defense.
#
# Without this patch, EAP-AKA silently falls back to the DEFAULT RES/CK/IK
# (or crashes) and the ePDG rejects authentication (EAP FAILURE).
